ls(list) - displays information about files in directory
pwd (print working directory)- displays working directory
mkdir (make directory)- create a directory -> mkdir directory_name
rmdir (remove directory)- removes directories -> rmdir directory_name
cd (change directory)- navigate between folder -> cd directory_name
cp (copy)- moves files from directory to another -> cp file_name directory_name
mv (move) - rename and replace the files -> mv file_name new_file_name
rm (remove) - delete files -> rm file_name
uname (Unix name) - command to get basic information about OS -> uname -a (displays all available information)
locate - find a file in the db -> locate file_name
touch - create empty file -> touch file_name
ln (link) - create shortcuts to other files -> ln existing_file_name hard_link
cat (concatenate) - display file contents on terminla -> cat file_name
clear - clear terminal
ps(process status) - Display the processes in terminal
man - access manual for all linux commands
grep(global regular expression print) - search for a specific string in an output -> grep "string_name" file_name
echo - display active processes on the terminal
wget (web get)- download files from internet - wget http://example.com/file.zip
whoami - prints user| create or update passwords for existing users -> whoami | passwd$(whoami) (for pw) 



